'''João Pedro Cavaco Cancelo''' (born 27 May 1994) is a Portuguese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] or [[left-back]] for {{Spanish football updater|Barcelona}} club [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], on loan from [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Hilal SFC|Al Hilal]], and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe279932/joao-cancelo/ |title=João Cancelo: Profile |website=WorldFootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |access-date=2 September 2023}}</ref>

After spending most of his youth career at [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], Cancelo began his professional senior career with them, before moving to [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] permanently in May 2015. After a loan to [[Inter Milan]] in August 2017, [[Derby d'Italia|Italian rivals]] [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] signed him the following June, winning a [[Serie A]] title and the [[Supercoppa Italiana]] with them. In the summer of 2019, Cancelo joined [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], he made 154 appearances for the club, and won the [[UEFA Champions League]], three [[Premier League]] titles, two [[EFL Cup|League Cups]], and one [[FA Cup]]. In the [[2020–21 Manchester City F.C. season|2020–21 season]], he played a significant role in Manchester City reaching their first [[2021 UEFA Champions League final|UEFA Champions League final]]. 

In January 2023, he was loaned to [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], winning a [[Bundesliga]] title, while being part of City's [[2022–23 Manchester City F.C. season|team]] that won [[Treble (association football)|continental treble]], and [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in August. The following August, Cancelo signed for Saudi club Al-Hilal, only to return to Barcelona on loan in January 2026, winning a [[La Liga]] title, making him the only player to win league titles in all of Europe's [[Big Five (association football)|top four leagues]].

Cancelo made his senior debut for Portugal in 2016, after previously being [[Cap (association football)|capped]] by the nations's all youth team levels, being part of the [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21]] team that reached the [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship final|2015 UEFA European Championship final]]. He was chosen in Portugal's squads for one [[FIFA World Cup]] ([[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]]) and one [[UEFA European Championship]] ([[UEFA Euro 2024|2024]]). He was chosen in Portugal's squad for the [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals]] on home soil, winning the inaugural edition of the competition with his nation.

==Club career==
===Benfica===
Born in [[Barreiro, Portugal|Barreiro]], Setúbal District, Cancelo started playing football with local club [[F.C. Barreirense|Barreirense]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/benfica-tambem-lucra-com-a-transferencia-de-cancelo.html|title=Benfica também lucra com a transferência de Cancelo|trans-title=Benfica also profit from Cancelo's transfer|newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|language=pt|date=27 June 2018|access-date=4 July 2018|archive-date=4 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704123551/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/benfica-tambem-lucra-com-a-transferencia-de-cancelo.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He joined [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]'s youth system in 2007 at the age of 13, where he played at [[Full back (association football)|full back]].{{citation needed|date=March 2023}}

On 28 July 2012, Cancelo made his debut with Benfica's first team in a [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] against [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]] where he played the full 90 minutes as a right back.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jn.pt/PaginaInicial/Desporto/Interior.aspx?content_id=2692273|title=Nélson Oliveira e Cancelo titulares|trans-title=Nélson Oliveira and Cancelo start|newspaper=[[Jornal de Notícias]]|last=Gomes|first=José Pedro|language=pt|date=28 July 2012|access-date=4 August 2012|archive-date=4 April 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130404221021/http://www.jn.pt/PaginaInicial/Desporto/Interior.aspx?content_id=2692273|url-status=live}}</ref> Despite being registered with [[S.L. Benfica B|the reserve team]], he was touted as a possible replacement to [[Maxi Pereira]] in the seniors;<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/vieira-confirma-joao-cancelo-para-a-lateral-direita-2683916.html|title=Vieira confirma João Cancelo para a lateral-direita|trans-title=Vieira confirms João Cancelo for right-back|newspaper=Jornal de Notícias|last1=Lousada Oliveira|first1=Otávio|last2=Fernandes|first2=Nuno|language=pt|date=24 July 2012|access-date=4 August 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107070822/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/vieira-confirma-joao-cancelo-para-a-lateral-direita-2683916.html|archive-date=7 January 2014}}</ref> until 2013 he also represented [[S.L. Benfica Juniors|the juniors]], and on 18 May of that year he scored the two decisive goals in a 2–1 win over [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]] to win the national championship.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://expresso.sapo.pt/comentario-benfica-garante-titulo-nacional-de-juniores-com-bis-de-joao-cancelo=f808015|title=Benfica garante título nacional de juniores com "bis" de João Cancelo|trans-title=Benfica confirm national juniors title with brace from João Cancelo|newspaper=[[Expresso (newspaper)|Expresso]]|language=pt|date=18 May 2013|access-date=24 May 2013|archive-date=9 November 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109004233/http://expresso.sapo.pt/comentario-benfica-garante-titulo-nacional-de-juniores-com-bis-de-joao-cancelo=f808015|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Cancelo played his first competitive game with Benfica's main squad on 25 January 2014, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in the [[2013–14 Taça da Liga|1–0 home success]] against Gil Vicente for the [[Taça da Liga]],<ref name=JOGO>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/taca-liga/noticias/interior/sulejmani-manteve-o-benfica-vitorioso-3651733.html|title=Sulejmani manteve o Benfica vitorioso|trans-title=Sulejmani kept Benfica victorious|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|language=pt|date=25 January 2014|access-date=22 August 2017|archive-date=22 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170822101048/http://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/taca-liga/noticias/interior/sulejmani-manteve-o-benfica-vitorioso-3651733.html|url-status=live}}</ref> which was [[2014 Taça da Liga Final|later won]]. His maiden appearance in the [[Primeira Liga]] occurred on 10 May after they had already been crowned [[2013–14 Primeira Liga|league champions]], and he started in a 2–1 loss in ''[[O Clássico]]'' against [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref name=DN>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/futebol-nacional/interior/fc-porto-bate-benfica-sob-avaliacao-de-lopetegui-3855385.html|title=FC Porto bate Benfica sob avaliação de Lopetegui|trans-title=FC Porto beat Benfica as Lopetegui looks on|newspaper=[[Diário de Notícias]]|last=Ruela|first=João|language=pt|date=10 May 2014|access-date=19 February 2016|archive-date=8 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208111853/http://www.dn.pt/desporto/futebol-nacional/interior/fc-porto-bate-benfica-sob-avaliacao-de-lopetegui-3855385.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Valencia===
====2014–16: Debut season and regular starter====
[[File:Valencia-Zenit (1).jpg|thumb|upright|Cancelo playing for [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in 2015]]
On 20 August 2014, Cancelo joined [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] on a one-year [[Loan (association football)|loan]] with the option to purchase for €15 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valenciacf.com/ver/36900/comunicado-oficial-joao-cancelo.html|title=Comunicado oficial: Joao Cancelo|trans-title=Official announcement: Joao Cancelo|publisher=Valencia CF|language=es|date=20 August 2014|access-date=20 August 2014|archive-date=27 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627012931/http://www.valenciacf.com/ver/36900/comunicado-oficial-joao-cancelo.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Although his economic rights were owned by [[Peter Lim]], a loan was arranged to take him to Valencia due to Lim's purchase of the latter club.<ref>{{cite web|title = Joao Cancelo, the first signing of Peter Lim for Valencia|url = http://www.futbol.as.com/futbol/2014/08/14/primera/1408052614_038235.html|year = 2014|access-date = 26 June 2018|newspaper = [[AS (newspaper)|AS]]|archive-date = 4 March 2016|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304001401/http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2014/08/14/primera/1408052614_038235.html|url-status = dead}}</ref> 

His [[La Liga]] debut occurred on 25 September, playing the entirety of a 3–0 home win over [[Córdoba CF|Córdoba]];<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2014_15/primera/jornada_5/val_cor/|title=Líder no hay más que Nuno|trans-title=There's no leader like Nuno|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|last=Egea|first=Pablo|language=es|date=25 September 2014|access-date=19 February 2016|archive-date=21 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160221085019/http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2014_15/primera/jornada_5/val_cor/|url-status=live}}</ref> He initially started as a substitute and appeared in the round of 16 round of the [[2014–15 Copa del Rey|Copa del Rey]] in the first leg against [[Rayo Vallecano]]. He would also occasionally move to the [[Midfielder#Winger|right wing]] and later his good performances, specially against [[Levante UD|Levante]] on 12 April 2015, in which he was awarded the man of the match.<ref>{{Cite web|title=First great night of Cancelo|url=http://www.levante-emv.com/valencia-cf/2015/04/15/primera-gran-noche-cancelo/1250960.html|access-date=26 June 2018|author=Levante-EMV|date=15 April 2015|author-link=Levante-EMV|archive-date=27 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627034422/https://www.levante-emv.com/valencia-cf/2015/04/15/primera-gran-noche-cancelo/1250960.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=MAN OF THE MATCH: CANCELO |url=http://www.vcfplay.com/match/match-cancelo-5870.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627005732/http://www.vcfplay.com/match/match-cancelo-5870.html |archive-date=27 June 2018 |access-date=26 June 2018}}</ref> Throughout [[2014–15 La Liga|the season]], he was used a second-choice right back behind [[Antonio Barragán]], finishing the season with 13 appearances, across all competitions. Cancelo's performances helped Valencia reach the [[2015–16 UEFA Champions League]], leading him, on 25 May, to agree to a permanent contract with the club until 30 June 2021, for a transfer fee of €15 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/41904/language/pt-PT/.aspx|title=João Cancelo transferido para o Valência CF|trans-title=João Cancelo transferred to Valencia CF|publisher=S.L. Benfica|language=pt|date=25 May 2015|access-date=25 May 2015|archive-date=25 May 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150525182752/http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/ArticleId/41904/language/pt-PT/.aspx|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.valenciacf.com/ver/41323/joao-cancelo-joins-valencia-cf-on-a-permanent-deal-through-to-2021.html|title=Joao Cancelo joins Valencia CF on a permanent deal through to 2021|publisher=Valencia CF|date=25 May 2015|access-date=25 May 2015|archive-date=28 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180628015746/http://en.valenciacf.com/ver/41323/joao-cancelo-joins-valencia-cf-on-a-permanent-deal-through-to-2021.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/slb/sad/ofertas_pub/-/media/benficadp/Images/generic_content_pages/slb/SAD/ofertas_publicas_distribuicao/fsd150611.pdf|title=Prospeto de "Benfica SAD 2016–2019"|trans-title=Prospect of "Benfica PLSC 2016–2019"|publisher=S.L. Benfica|language=pt|location=Lisbon|date=15 April 2016|access-date=22 August 2017|page=66|archive-date=22 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170822174113/https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/slb/sad/ofertas_pub/-/media/benficadp/Images/generic_content_pages/slb/SAD/ofertas_publicas_distribuicao/fsd150611.pdf|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abola.pt/clubes/ver.aspx?t=3&id=550925|url-status=dead|title=João Cancelo vendido ao Valência por 15 milhões de euros|trans-title=João Cancelo sold to Valencia for 15 million euros|newspaper=[[A Bola]]|language=pt|date=25 May 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150702123142/http://www.abola.pt/clubes/ver.aspx?t=3&id=550925|archive-date=2 July 2015|access-date=11 July 2015}}</ref>

In the [[2015–16 La Liga|following season]], Cancelo became a starter earning his debut in the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] on 16 September, where he scored his first goal for ''Los Che'' in a [[2015–16 UEFA Champions League|2–3 home loss]] to [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]]. In doing so, he became the fifth youngest scorer in Valencia's history in the Champions League (aged 21 years and 107 days).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0225-0e91b7eb2dac-16b446b04e30-1000--witsel-breaks-valencia-hearts-in-five-goal-thriller/|title=Witsel breaks Valencia hearts in five-goal thriller|publisher=UEFA|date=16 September 2016|access-date=25 November 2016|archive-date=23 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160123143553/http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000634/match=2015679/postmatch/report/index.html#zenit+valencia|url-status=live}}</ref> On 2 December, Cancelo scored his first goal [[2015–16 Copa del Rey|Copa del Rey]] in a 3–1 victory over [[Barakaldo CF|Barakaldo]]. Valencia was eliminated from the tournament after losing 8–1 on aggregate to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web|title=El Barça enciende la consola|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2015_16/copa/semifinal/ida/bar_val/|website=Marca.com|access-date=3 February 2016|date=3 February 2016|archive-date=3 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203090922/http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2015_16/copa/semifinal/ida/bar_val/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Valencia 1-1 Barcelona (agg 1-8): Neville denied rare win as Barça break record|url=http://www.goal.com/en/match/valencia-vs-barcelona/2196369/report?ICID=MP_MS_5|website=goal.com|access-date=10 February 2016|archive-date=18 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318190324/http://www.goal.com/en/match/valencia-vs-barcelona/2196369/report?ICID=MP_MS_5|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Barça salvage 1-1 King's Cup draw against improved Valencia|date=10 February 2016|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-spain-cup-idUKKCN0VJ2OG|work=[[Reuters]]|access-date=10 February 2016|archive-date=15 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815125119/https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-spain-cup-idUKKCN0VJ2OG|url-status=dead}}</ref> He also netted for the first time in the league the following 20 April to conclude a 4–0 win over [[SD Eibar|Eibar]] at the [[Mestalla Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2015_16/la-liga/jornada_34/val_eib/|title=1, 2, 3, Alcácer otra vez|trans-title=1, 2, 3, Alcácer again|newspaper=Marca|last=Hurtado|first=José Luis|language=es|date=20 April 2016|access-date=25 November 2016|archive-date=26 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161126065456/http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2015_16/la-liga/jornada_34/val_eib/|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2016–17: Final season with Valencia====
In the [[2016–17 La Liga|2016–17 season]], Cancelo's performances slightly declined, with Cancelo making an error leading him to conceding a penalty in Valencia's first league match in a 2–4 loss against [[UD Las Palmas|Las Palmas]]. Despite his errors, Cancelo's performances improved, leading him to be used more often with new coach [[Cesare Prandelli]], changing his position to the right-wing.<ref>{{cite web|title=João Cancelo as an unbalancing factor|url=http://www.superdeporte.es/valencia/2016/10/18/joao-cancelo-factor-desequilibrante/313663.html|access-date=26 June 2018|author=Superdeporte|date=18 October 2016|archive-date=27 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627062315/https://www.superdeporte.es/valencia/2016/10/18/joao-cancelo-factor-desequilibrante/313663.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Cancelo was fixed in the eleven throughout the season, playing almost the same number of games between the right back and the right wing. On 2 April he scored his first league goal in a 3–0 victory against [[Deportivo La Coruña]]. Afterwards, Cancelo made a "[[List of gestures#Mouth|shush]]" gesture towards Valencia's fans, who criticized him for his defensive errors, but he immediately apologized for the gesture.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cancelo shuts fans at the Mestalla and apologizes|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20170402/421407193293/cancelo-lia-mandar-callar-mestalla-pide-disculpas.html|access-date=27 June 2018|author=La Vanguardia|date=2 April 2017|author-link=La Vanguardia|archive-date=28 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180628015609/http://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20170402/421407193293/cancelo-lia-mandar-callar-mestalla-pide-disculpas.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2017–18: Loan to Inter Milan====
On 22 August 2017, Cancelo joined [[Inter Milan]] on a one-year loan until 30 June 2018 with the option of making the move permanent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inter.it/en/news/59321/cancelo-is-an-inter-player|title=Cancelo is an Inter player!|publisher=Inter Milan|date=22 August 2017|access-date=23 August 2017|archive-date=22 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180622111519/https://www.inter.it/en/news/59321/cancelo-is-an-inter-player|url-status=dead}}</ref> The deal was part of a loan exchange, with [[Geoffrey Kondogbia]] moving in the other direction.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/108594/official-inter-sign-cancelo|title=Official: Inter sign Cancelo|publisher=Football Italia|date=22 August 2017|access-date=23 August 2017|archive-date=23 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823120737/http://www.football-italia.net/108594/official-inter-sign-cancelo|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his [[Serie A]] debut four days later, replacing [[Antonio Candreva]] in the 83rd minute of a 3–1 win away to [[AS Roma|Roma]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.quotidiano.net/sport/calcio/roma-inter-1.3355556|title=Roma-Inter 1–3, Icardi spegne i sogni giallorossi|trans-title=Roma-Inter 1–3, Icardi puts an end to yellow-and-red dreams|publisher=[[Quotidiano.net]]|last=Bocchini|first=Francesco|language=it|date=26 August 2017|access-date=27 August 2017|archive-date=28 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828061606/http://www.quotidiano.net/sport/calcio/roma-inter-1.3355556|url-status=live}}</ref>

Cancelo suffered a knee ligament injury in late August 2017 while on international duty, going on to be sidelined for one-and-a-half months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/inter-portugal-joao-cancelo-knee-injury/7gw8bf5hqvp012zffut0tq411|title=Inter confirm knee ligament injury for new boy Cancelo|publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=31 August 2017|access-date=31 August 2017|archive-date=30 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170830190324/http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/inter-portugal-joao-cancelo-knee-injury/7gw8bf5hqvp012zffut0tq411|url-status=live}}</ref> He returned to action during the 3–2 home victory over [[A.C. Milan|AC Milan]] in the [[Derby della Madonnina]], featuring 20 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/club/internazionale/110/blog/post/3230977/mauro-icardi-gets-10-10-as-hat-trick-earns-inter-win-against-milan|title=Mauro Icardi gets 10/10 as hat trick earns Inter win against Milan|publisher=ESPN FC|date=17 October 2017|access-date=17 October 2017|archive-date=18 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171018014254/http://www.espnfc.com/club/internazionale/110/blog/post/3230977/mauro-icardi-gets-10-10-as-hat-trick-earns-inter-win-against-milan|url-status=live}}</ref> After a few weeks of adaptation in the [[Serie A]], Cancelo made his debut as a starter at the [[2017–18 Coppa Italia|Coppa Italia]] in a home victory against [[Pordenone Calcio|Pordenone]]. On 17 April 2018, he scored his first league goal with a free kick in a 4–0 home victory over [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.passioneinter.com/notizie-nerazzurre/cancelo-contento-per-il-primo-gol-in-nerazzurro-ora-abbiamo-gare-difficili-ma-lobiettivo-e-la-champions/|title=Cancelo: "Happy for the first goal in the Nerazzurri. Now we have only one goal!"|date=17 April 2017|access-date=17 April 2017|archive-date=19 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180619040208/http://www.passioneinter.com/notizie-nerazzurre/cancelo-contento-per-il-primo-gol-in-nerazzurro-ora-abbiamo-gare-difficili-ma-lobiettivo-e-la-champions/|url-status=live}}</ref>

During his phase of adaptation in Serie A, in which was added some tactical misunderstanding, his performances began progressively improving, leading him to be included in [[Serie A Team of the Year#2017–18|Serie A's Team of the Year]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/131574/serie-team-2017-18|title=Serie A Team of 2017–18|date=3 December 2018|website=Football Italia|access-date=3 December 2018|archive-date=4 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204101933/https://www.football-italia.net/131574/serie-team-2017-18|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sport.sky.it/calcio/serie-a/2018/03/19/5-azioni-di-cancelo-contro-la-sampdoria.html|title=Inter, 5 shares of Cancelo against Sampdoria|date=18 March 2018|access-date=18 March 2018|archive-date=24 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180924190215/https://sport.sky.it/calcio/serie-a/2018/03/19/5-azioni-di-cancelo-contro-la-sampdoria.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://grangala.assocalciatori.it/Vincitori/joao-cancelo/|title=Joao Cancelo ⋆ Great Football Gal|date=11 December 2018|access-date=11 December 2018|archive-date=14 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181214065432/http://grangala.assocalciatori.it/Vincitori/joao-cancelo/|url-status=live}}</ref> Despite his good performances during the season, the club opted to not buy Cancelo.<ref>{{cite web |date=26 April 2019 |title=Inter-Juve, sliding doors Cancelo: chi ha scelto bene? |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/26-04-2019/juve-cancelo-stagione-alti-bassi-bocciato-o-promosso-3301075377433.shtml |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905203316/https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/26-04-2019/juve-cancelo-stagione-alti-bassi-bocciato-o-promosso-3301075377433.shtml |archive-date=5 September 2019 |access-date=15 September 2019 |language=it}}</ref>

===Juventus===
[[File:Icc-11 43156863954 o (50121473296).jpg|thumb|Cancelo playing for [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] in 2018]]
On 27 June 2018, Cancelo was signed by [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] on a five-year contract for €40.4 million,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2018/joao-cancelo-joins-juventus.php|title=João Cancelo signs for Juventus!|publisher=Juventus F.C.|date=27 June 2018|access-date=27 June 2018|archive-date=30 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190430194403/https://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2018/joao-cancelo-joins-juventus.php|url-status=live}}</ref> making his domestic league debut on 18 August in a 3–2 away win against [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo Verona]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lastampa.it/2018/08/18/sport/la-juve-soffre-ma-batte-il-chievo-al-bentegodi-decide-bernardeschi-in-rimonta-wCtLRb2ptVKdd2faY3mtJM/pagina.html|title=La Juve soffre ma batte il Chievo, al Bentegodi decide Bernardeschi in rimonta|trans-title=Juve suffer but beat Chievo, Bernardeschi settles it at Bentegodi in comeback|newspaper=[[La Stampa]]|last=Oddenino|first=Gianluca|language=it|date=18 August 2018|access-date=18 August 2018|archive-date=3 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403174507/https://www.lastampa.it/2018/08/18/sport/la-juve-soffre-ma-batte-il-chievo-al-bentegodi-decide-bernardeschi-in-rimonta-wCtLRb2ptVKdd2faY3mtJM/pagina.html|url-status=live}}</ref> 

He scored his first league goal the same month, as his team came from behind to defeat [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] 2–1 at the [[Stadio Olimpico]] in Rome; he also helped win the decisive match-winning [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty]] later during the same game, which was subsequently converted by compatriot [[Cristiano Ronaldo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/125269|title=Lazio 1–2 Juventus|publisher=Football Italia|date=27 January 2019|access-date=28 January 2019|archive-date=28 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190128082841/https://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/125269|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/27-01-2019/juventus-allegri-cambia-match-coi-cambi-serataccia-emre-can-320723377020.shtml|title=Juventus, Allegri cambia il match coi cambi. Serataccia per Emre Can|trans-title=Juventus, Allegri livens match with changes. Nightmare for Emre Can|newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|last=Bianchin|first=Luca|language=it|date=27 January 2019|access-date=28 January 2019|archive-date=21 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190421140130/https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/27-01-2019/juventus-allegri-cambia-match-coi-cambi-serataccia-emre-can-320723377020.shtml|url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 October, Cancelo provided an assist for [[Rodrigo Bentancur]] in a 2–0 away win over [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/128987/bentancur-enjoys-debut-juve-goal |title=Bentancur enjoys debut Juve goal |publisher=Football Italia |date=6 October 2018 |access-date=6 October 2018 |archive-date=6 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181006235502/https://www.football-italia.net/128987/bentancur-enjoys-debut-juve-goal |url-status=live }}</ref> On 7 December, Cancelo provided an assist for [[Mario Mandžukić]] in a 1–0 home win against his former club [[Inter Milan]] in the [[Derby d'Italia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1317650/Live/Italy-Serie-A-2018-2019-Juventus-Inter |title=Bentancur enjoys debut Juve goal |publisher=Football Italia |date=7 December 2018 |access-date=8 October 2018 |archive-date=11 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811182722/https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1317650/Live/Italy-Serie-A-2018-2019-Juventus-Inter |url-status=live }}</ref>

He won his first trophy with the club in January 2019, featuring the entire [[2018 Supercoppa Italiana|1–0 victory]] over Milan for the [[Supercoppa Italiana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/46897172|title=Juventus 1–0 AC Milan: Cristiano Ronaldo header wins Supercoppa for Juve|website=[[BBC Sport]]|date=16 January 2019|access-date=28 April 2019|archive-date=10 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190310174046/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/46897172|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2816026-cristiano-ronaldo-wins-1st-juventus-trophy-scores-in-super-cup-against-milan|title=Cristiano Ronaldo wins 1st Juventus trophy, scores in Super Cup against Milan|publisher=[[Bleacher Report]]|last=Verschueren|first=Gianni|date=16 January 2019|access-date=28 April 2019|archive-date=3 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190203113002/https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2816026-cristiano-ronaldo-wins-1st-juventus-trophy-scores-in-super-cup-against-milan|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Burnton |first=Simon |date=16 January 2019 |title=Juventus 1–0 Milan: Supercoppa Italiana – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2019/jan/16/juventus-v-milan-supercoppa-italiana-live |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412120628/https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2019/jan/16/juventus-v-milan-supercoppa-italiana-live |archive-date=12 April 2019 |access-date=28 April 2019 |newspaper=The Guardian |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 10 April, Cancelo provided an assist for his compatriot Cristiano Ronaldo in a 1–1 away draw in the first leg of Juventus' [[2018–19 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] quarter-final against [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], on 10 April.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47884839|title=Cristiano Ronaldo's Champions League record – can Lionel Messi match it?|website=BBC Sport|date=11 April 2019|access-date=11 April 2019|archive-date=13 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413145457/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47884839|url-status=live}}</ref> In the second leg in Turin on 16 April, Juventus eventually lost the match 2–1, and were eliminated from the competition.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47939282 |title=Juventus 1–2 Ajax (agg 2–3) |website=BBC Sport |last1=Henson |first1=Mike |date=16 April 2019 |access-date=17 April 2019 |archive-date=30 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190430093905/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47939282 |url-status=live }}</ref> Four days later, Cancelo played in the ''[[List of Italian football champions|Scudetto]]''-clinching match against [[ACF Fiorentina–Juventus F.C. rivalry|rivals]] [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]], as Juventus won their eighth successive league title after a 2–1 home triumph.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-sg/match/juventus-v-fiorentina/report/3plhazl81l75b7ysmwn34hu22|title=Juventus 2 Fiorentina 1: Bianconeri bounce back to seal Scudetto|publisher=Goal|last=Dorman|first=Matt|date=20 April 2019|access-date=28 April 2019|archive-date=21 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190421041142/https://www.goal.com/en-sg/match/juventus-v-fiorentina/report/3plhazl81l75b7ysmwn34hu22|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Manchester City===
====2019–23: Struggles, consecutive Premier League titles and European Final====
On 7 August 2019, Cancelo signed for [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] on a six-year contract worth £27.4&nbsp;million plus [[Danilo (footballer, born July 1991)|Danilo]] being sent to Juventus in part-exchange, equalling to £60&nbsp;million, making him the [[List of most expensive association football transfers|most expensive]] right back ever.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/manchestercity/man-city-sign-joao-cancelo-from-juventus-with-danilo-in-partexchange-a4206581.html|title=Man City sign Joao Cancelo as Danilo heads to Juventus in part-exchange|date=7 August 2019|publisher=Standard|access-date=7 August 2019|archive-date=8 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808142906/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/manchestercity/man-city-sign-joao-cancelo-from-juventus-with-danilo-in-partexchange-a4206581.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/man-city-and-juventus-confirm-cancelo-danilo-swap-in-65m/ga32ehdxuelk1qso2ayr89hge|title=Man City and Juventus confirm Cancelo-Danilo swap in €65m deal|publisher=Goal|access-date=7 August 2019|archive-date=7 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190807200729/https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/man-city-and-juventus-confirm-cancelo-danilo-swap-in-65m/ga32ehdxuelk1qso2ayr89hge|url-status=live}}</ref> 

On 25 August, he made his Premier League debut against [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] appearing as a late substitute for [[Kyle Walker]] in a 3–1 victory. On 18 December, he scored his first goal for City in a 3–1 away win over [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]] in the [[2019–20 EFL Cup|quarter-finals]] of the [[EFL Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50738362|title=Oxford United 1-3 Manchester City: Raheem Sterling double seals semi-final spot|website=BBC Sport|date=18 December 2019|access-date=18 December 2019|archive-date=20 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201220120232/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50738362|url-status=live}}</ref> Initially, Cancelo struggled during his first season in the club, looking out of position in the matches he played and failing to seal a starting spot in the team due to competing against [[Kyle Walker]] for a right-back spot.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/manchestercity/news/joao-cancelo-makes-positional-offer-to-pep-guardiola-during-discussion-over-manchester-city-versatility|title = Joao Cancelo Makes Positional Offer to Pep Guardiola During Discussion over Man City Versatility|magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]]|first=Vayam|last=Lahoti|date=4 October 2021|access-date=29 May 2022}}</ref>

On 17 October 2020, Cancelo made his first league start for the new season after an injury in a 1–0 home win over [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]. On 3 November, he scored his first Champions League goal for City in a 3–0 home win over [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League group stage|group stage]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54784118|title=Manchester City 3-0 Olympiakos: Gabriel Jesus returns to seal third win in Champions League|website=BBC Sport|date=3 November 2020|access-date=3 November 2020|archive-date=8 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108174429/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54784118|url-status=live}}</ref> and on 26 January 2021, he scored his first Premier League goal in a 5–0 away win over [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/55714078|title=West Bromwich Albion 0-5 Manchester City|website=BBC Sport|date=26 January 2021|access-date=26 January 2021|archive-date=20 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210420103459/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/55714078|url-status=live}}</ref> On 24 February, he was named man of the match, after providing an assist to [[Bernardo Silva]] in Manchester City's 2–0 away win over [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]] in the first leg of the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|round of 16]] tie.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Rostance|first=Tom|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56172096|title=Borussia Monchengladbach 0-2 Man City: 19 wins in a row for Pep Guardiola's side|date=24 February 2021|website=BBC Sport|access-date=24 February 2021|archive-date=1 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501033202/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56172096|url-status=live}}</ref>

During the season, Cancelo's ability to come inside from full back to maintain control of the ball in central midfield position, while ensuring his team was in a more stable defensive shape when possession was lost, was praised as being one of the key factors in Manchester City regaining the Premier League title that season, while also being named in the [[PFA Team of the Year|PFA Premier League Team of the Year]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/57356719|title=PFA Premier League Team of the Year: Kevin de Bruyne one of six Manchester City players picked|website=BBC Sport|date=4 June 2021|access-date=4 June 2021|archive-date=5 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210605060605/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/57356719|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Manchester City win Premier League title after Manchester United lose to Leicester|website=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56964843|date=27 February 2021|access-date=12 May 2021|archive-date=14 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210514195830/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56964843|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 17 October 2021, Cancelo scored his first goal of the season for City in a 6–3 home [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] group stage win against [[RB Leipzig]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Dias to be one of Man City's five captains this season|publisher=Sky Sports|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12410930/ruben-dias-pep-guardiola-makes-man-city-defender-one-of-his-five-captains-this-season|date=18 September 2021|access-date=18 September 2021|archive-date=18 September 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210918092615/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12410930/ruben-dias-pep-guardiola-makes-man-city-defender-one-of-his-five-captains-this-season|url-status=live}}</ref> On 3 November, Cancelo provided a [[hat-trick]] of assists for [[Phil Foden]], [[Riyad Mahrez]] and [[Gabriel Jesus]] in a 4–1 Champions League group stage home victory against [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]], leading him to be named man of the match.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11945/12459044/man-city-4-1-club-brugge-pep-guardiolas-side-on-brink-of-champions-league-last-16-qualification|title=Man City 4-1 Club Brugge: Pep Guardiola's side on brink of Champions League last-16 qualification|publisher=Sky Sports|date=3 November 2021|access-date=3 November 2021|archive-date=3 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211103234014/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11945/12459044/man-city-4-1-club-brugge-pep-guardiolas-side-on-brink-of-champions-league-last-16-qualification|url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 November, in the [[Manchester derby]], Cancelo created both goals in a 2–0 victory against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] at [[Old Trafford]], forcing an [[Eric Bailly]] own goal and providing an assist for [[Bernardo Silva]], for his fifth assist of the season in two games.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-united-joao-cancelo-transfer-22099277|title=Why Manchester United rejected Joao Cancelo transfer five years ago|publisher=[[Manchester Evening News]]|date=8 November 2021|access-date=8 November 2021|archive-date=8 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211108130102/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-united-joao-cancelo-transfer-22099277|url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 December, on his 100th appearance for the club, he scored a long-range shot and provided an assist in a 4–0 win against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/newcastle-vs-man-city-result-premier-league-2021-joao-cancelo-b972827.html%3famp|title=Newcastle 0-4 Man City: Joao Cancelo rocket helps secure Christmas top spot|access-date=29 December 2021|archive-date=19 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211219155152/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/newcastle-vs-man-city-result-premier-league-2021-joao-cancelo-b972827.html?amp|url-status=dead}}</ref>

[[File:CanceloCity23.jpg|thumb|upright|Cancelo playing for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in 2023]]
Following the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], in January 2023, it was reported by ''[[The Athletic]]'' that Cancelo had fallen out with his manager [[Pep Guardiola]] over a lack of playing time. He had begun losing his place to in the starting eleven to [[Nathan Aké]] and [[Rico Lewis]], after returning from the tournament. After again featuring on the bench for the third game in a row in a [[2022–23 FA Cup|FA Cup]] match against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], their relationship reached the breaking point, which led to Cancelo being told to leave the club by Guardiola.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4138939/2023/01/31/joao-cancelo-how-man-city-career-came-to-a-sudden-end-with-shock-bayern-munich-move/ |title=Joao Cancelo: How Man City career came to a sudden end with shock Bayern Munich move |work=[[The Athletic]] |date=31 January 2023 |access-date=5 June 2023 |archive-date=5 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230605005125/https://theathletic.com/4138939/2023/01/31/joao-cancelo-how-man-city-career-came-to-a-sudden-end-with-shock-bayern-munich-move/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2022–23: Loan to Bayern Munich====
On 31 January, Cancelo was loaned to [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] for the remainder of the season with an option to buy for €70 million (£61.6 million).<ref>{{Cite web |date=31 January 2023 |title=FC Bayern sign João Cancelo on loan |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/01/fc-bayern-sign-joao-cancelo-on-loan-from-manchester-city |access-date=31 January 2023 |publisher=FC Bayern München |archive-date=26 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226084844/https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/01/fc-bayern-sign-joao-cancelo-on-loan-from-manchester-city |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/joao-cancelo-bayern-munich-manchester-city-transfer-63810760|title=Cancelo joins Bayern Munich on loan|publisher=Manchester City F.C.|date=31 January 2023|access-date=31 January 2022|archive-date=31 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230131112648/https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/joao-cancelo-bayern-munich-manchester-city-transfer-63810760|url-status=live}}</ref>

Cancelo made his debut for Bayern in a 4–0 [[DFB-Pokal]] win over [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]], registering an assist for [[Eric Maxim Choupo-Moting]]'s goal.<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 February 2023 |title=Nagelsmann on Cancelo: 'He carried out what we wanted' |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/02/cancelo-dream-debut-at-mainz |access-date=1 February 2023 |publisher=FC Bayern München |archive-date=2 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230202123153/https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/02/cancelo-dream-debut-at-mainz |url-status=live }}</ref> On 11 March, he scored his first goal the club in a 5–3 win over [[FC Augsburg|Augsburg]] in the [[2022–23 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64928867 |title=Bayern Munich 5–3 FC Augsburg |work=BBC Sport |date=11 March 2023 |access-date=12 March 2023 |archive-date=12 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230312122059/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64928867 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 12 April, having been drawn against each other in the quarter-finals of the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]], Cancelo came on as an 80th-minute substitute against parent club Manchester City as Bayern were defeated 3–0 in the first leg at the [[City of Manchester Stadium|Etihad Stadium]]. During the match, Cancelo was booed by sections of the City supporters, leading Guardiola to defend him against the criticism, reminding that he had been an important player for Manchester City in the previous seasons and that his "quality was undeniable".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-news-joao-cancelo-26700448 |title=Pep Guardiola responds to Joao Cancelo boos from Man City fans |work=[[Manchester Evening News]] |date=15 April 2023 |access-date=29 May 2023 |archive-date=29 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230529090752/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-news-joao-cancelo-26700448 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Kelsey |first=George |title=Haaland surpasses long-standing Premier League goal record |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/Haaland%20surpasses%20long-standing%20Premier%20League%20goal%20record |access-date=12 April 2023 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> The following week on 19 April, Bayern were knocked out 4–1 on aggregate following a 1–1 draw in the second leg, with Cancelo starting the game before being replaced in the 63rd minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65317810 |title=Bayern vs Man City |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=19 April 2023 |access-date=5 June 2023 |archive-date=31 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230531215427/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65317810 |url-status=live }}</ref> 

On 27 May, Cancelo played the full 90 minutes of a 2–1 victory over [[1. FC Köln|FC Köln]], to clinch the 11th consecutive league title for his club ahead of rivals [[Borussia Dortmund]] on goal difference.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dw.com/en/bayern-munich-champions-again-after-dortmund-meltdown/a-65753627 |title=Bayern Munich champions again after Dortmund meltdown |publisher=DW |date=27 May 2023 |access-date=5 June 2023 |archive-date=5 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230605004536/https://www.dw.com/en/bayern-munich-champions-again-after-dortmund-meltdown/a-65753627 |url-status=live }}</ref> Cancelo became the third player, after [[Daniel Amartey]] and [[David Beckham]], to win two league titles in different countries in a single season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/joao-cancelo-bundesliga-premier-league-two-winner-medal-in-one-season-reason-manchester-city-bayern-munich/article66904094.ece|title=Explained: How did Cancelo get winner's medal for Premier League and Bundesliga in one season|website=SportStar |date=28 May 2023 |access-date=6 December 2023}}</ref> He was also part of City's team that won the [[Treble (association football)#Continental trebles|continental treble]], having played half-season with them.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.sky.com/story/manchester-city-win-treble-with-1-0-champions-league-final-victory-over-inter-12900070 |title=A treble! Manchester City win Champions League, FA Cup and Premier League |publisher=Sky News |date=11 June 2023 |access-date=18 July 2023 |archive-date=18 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230718173446/https://news.sky.com/story/manchester-city-win-treble-with-1-0-champions-league-final-victory-over-inter-12900070 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of the season, Bayern opted to not activate Cancelo's buy-out clause, in order to prioritize funds for other signings, with his departure being confirmed by the club on 1 July.<ref>{{cite web |date=30 June 2023 |title=Bayern Múnich confirma las salidas de João Cancelo y Daley Blind |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/alemania/nota/_/id/12255578/bayern-munich-confirma-salidas-de-joao-cancelo-y-daley-blind |access-date=3 September 2023 |website=ESPN Deportes |language=es}}</ref>

====2023–24: Loan to Barcelona====
Following his loan move to Bayern, Cancelo rejoined Manchester City for pre-season, although he did not feature in any of City's opening three Premier League fixtures, the [[FA Community Shield]] or the [[UEFA Super Cup]], as he sought to finalise a move away from the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.90min.com/posts/joao-cancelo-joins-barcelona-on-loan-from-man-city |title=Joao Cancelo joins Barcelona on loan from Man City|work=90 Mins |date=1 September 2023|access-date=3 September 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Nakrani |first=Sachin |date=28 August 2023 |title=João Cancelo to complete loan move from Manchester City to Barcelona |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/28/joao-cancelo-to-complete-loan-move-from-manchester-city-to-barcelona |access-date=3 September 2023 |work=[[The Guardian]] |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 3 August, Cancelo agreed personal terms to join La Liga club Barcelona, with the club's manager [[Xavi (footballer, born 1980)|Xavi]], who wanted to sign him in January, identifying him as a priority target.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/es/noticias/joao-cancelo-agrees-personal-terms-with-european-giants-ahead-of-manchester-city-exit-37968280|title=JOAO CANCELO AGREES PERSONAL TERMS WITH EUROPEAN GIANTS AHEAD OF MANCHESTER CITY EXIT|work=[[One Football]]|date=3 August 2023|access-date=3 September 2023}}</ref> In the final moments of the summer transfer window, Bayern contacted Manchester City to potentially acquiring Cancelo on loan, due to Barcelona's financial difficulties involving La Liga's Financial Fair Play regulations, however, on 1 September, Barcelona confirmed the signing of Cancelo on a season-long loan, after La Liga accepted the financial guarantees offered by Barcelona's board, which in turn allowed him to be registered in La Liga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3664575/joao-cancelo-joins-fc-barcelona|title=João Cancelo joins FC Barcelona|publisher=FC Barcelona|date=1 September 2023|access-date=1 September 2023|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bulinews.com/news/18577/bayern-consider-renewed-cancelo-loan|title=Reports: Bayern consider renewed Cancelo loan|publisher=BuliNews.com|date=1 September 2023|access-date=3 September 2023|language=en}}</ref>

He made his debut two days later as a 59th-minute substitute in a 2–1 away win over [[Osasuna]].<ref name="Soccerway"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2023/09/03/spain/primera-division/club-atletico-osasuna/futbol-club-barcelona/4090881/ |title=Osasuna vs. Barcelona 1–2: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=3 September 2023}}</ref> On 16 September, Cancelo scored his first goal for the club, netting a strike from inside the box in his first start, as Barcelona's home league game against [[Real Betis]] ended in a dominant 5–0 win, which earned him the [[2023–24 La Liga#Awards|La Liga Goal of the Month]] award,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66834344|title=Barcelona 5–0 Real Betis: Barca go top of La Liga|publisher=BBC|work=BBC Sport|date=16 September 2023|access-date=17 September 2023}}</ref> followed by an assist and a last-minute winner, helping Barcelona overturn a two-goal deficit in a 3–2 home victory against [[Real Club Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]] on 23 September.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.telecomasia.net/news/football/lewandowski-sets-barcelonaundefineds-performance-record-in-21st-century/ |title=Lewandowski Sets Barcelona's Performance Record In 21st Century |website=telecomasia.net |author=Marina Magomedova |date=24 September 2023 |access-date=24 September 2023}}</ref> On 28 November, he scored and assisted in a 2–1 comeback at home against his first club's [[O Clássico|rivals]] [[FC Porto|Porto]] in the Champions League group stage, winning man of the match and securing the club's spot in the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|round of sixteen]] for the first time since [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League#Group stage|2020–21 season]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Barcelona 2-1 FC Porto (Nov 28, 2023) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/687607 |access-date=29 November 2023 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |date=28 November 2023 |title=Every UEFA Champions League Player of the Match {{!}} UEFA Champions League |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0285-1904c28d5633-377a22ec4306-1000--every-uefa-champions-league-player-of-the-match/ |access-date=29 November 2023 |website=[[UEFA]] |language=en}}</ref>

===Al-Hilal===
On 27 August 2024, Cancelo signed for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]] on a three-year contract in a deal reportedly worth £21.2m.<ref>{{cite web |title=Joao Cancelo joins Al Hilal |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/man-city-joao-cancelo-joins-al-hilal-63860374 |publisher=Manchester City |access-date=27 August 2024 |date=27 August 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=27 August 2024 |title=Joao Cancelo: Manchester City defender joins Saudi club Al-Hilal |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cd05ygv4gvno |access-date=27 August 2024 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Mott |first=Alex |date=27 August 2024 |title=Manchester City's João Cancelo completes permanent move to Al-Hilal |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/manchester-citys-joao-cancelo-completes-permanent-move-to-al-hilal-39953837 |access-date=27 August 2024 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref>

==== 2026: Second loan to Barcelona ====
On 13 January 2026, Barcelona announced that they had resigned Cancelo on loan for the rest of the [[2025–26 FC Barcelona season|season]],<ref name="Cancelo">{{cite news |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/4433204/joao-cancelo-passes-medical |title=João Cancelo passes medical |date=12 January 2026 |publisher=FC Barcelona |access-date=13 January 2026}}</ref> being handed the number 2 shirt.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-01-13 |title=Barcelona re-announce signing of Joao Cancelo just hours after deleting original confirmation of deal amid paperwork issue {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/barcelona-re-announce-signing-joao-cancelo-deleting-original-confirmation-paperwork-issue/blt946fea37ccf13432 |access-date=2026-01-13 |website=www.goal.com |language=en}}</ref> He made his second debut for the club on 19 January 2026, coming off the bench during an away game against Real Sociedad which Barcelona eventually lost 2–1.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Real Sociedad 2-1 Barcelona (18 Jan, 2026) Game Analysis - ESPN (UK) |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/748343 |access-date=2026-02-12 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> On 10 May, Cancelo played the full 90 minutes of a 2–0 victory over [[Real Madrid]] in ''[[El Clásico]]'', with Barcelona clinching their second consecutive league title. As a result, he became the first player to win four of five Europe's [[Big Five (association football)|top five leagues]] titles (only missing [[Ligue 1]]).<ref>{{Cite web |title=RBarcelona win second straight LaLiga title after El Clásico victory |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/48733610/arteta-says-brave-var-call-alter-arsenal-history |access-date=2026-05-10 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
[[File:João Cancelo (5) (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Cancelo playing for [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal U19]] in 2012]]

Cancelo represented [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal]] in the [[2012 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/seleccao/edgar-borges-convocatoria-portugal-europeu-sub-19/1354495-1194.html|title=Euro de sub-19: Sporting e Benfica em maioria nos convocados|trans-title=Under-19 Euro: Sporting and Benfica rule selection|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=pt|date=11 June 2012|access-date=4 August 2012|archive-date=6 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006072345/http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/seleccao/edgar-borges-convocatoria-portugal-europeu-sub-19/1354495-1194.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was also selected for [[2013 UEFA European Under-19 Championship|the following edition]] in Lithuania.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/Futebol/selecoes/interior.aspx?content_id=833181|title=Sub-19: Rui Silva substitui José Costa|trans-title=Under-19: Rui Silva replaces José Costa|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=14 July 2013|access-date=14 July 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924150341/http://www.record.xl.pt/Futebol/selecoes/interior.aspx?content_id=833181|archive-date=24 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>

With the [[Portugal national under-20 football team|under-20s]], Cancelo appeared at the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] and the [[2014 Toulon Tournament]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/Futebol/selecoes/interior.aspx?content_id=882916|title=Sub-20: Ilídio Vale convoca 20 para o Torneio de Toulon|trans-title=Under-20: Ilídio Vale calls 20 for Toulon Tournament|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=13 May 2013|access-date=24 May 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140516022919/http://www.record.xl.pt/Futebol/selecoes/interior.aspx?content_id=882916|archive-date=16 May 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> He featured in two games in the former competition, with the country reaching the [[Single-elimination tournament|round of 16]].{{citation needed|date=March 2023}}

Cancelo was part of the [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21 squad]] that competed in the [[2015 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]]. He replaced left-back [[Raphaël Guerreiro]] midway through the second half of the 5–0 semi-final win against [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany]] for his only appearance of the tournament,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/news/0257-0ded8b7c4c3e-2e039d18d446-1000--five-goal-portugal-stun-germany-in-semi-finals/|title=Five-goal Portugal stun Germany in semi-finals|publisher=UEFA|last=Hart|first=Simon|date=27 June 2015|access-date=19 February 2016|archive-date=3 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203141258/https://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2015/matches/round=2000409/match=2015382/postmatch/report/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref> in a final runner-up finish to [[Sweden national under-21 football team|Sweden]].<ref name=U21>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/news/0253-0d7ff6449831-1538840537e4-1000--spot-on-sweden-beat-portugal-to-win-u21-euro/|title=Spot-on Sweden beat Portugal to win U21 EURO|publisher=UEFA|last=Kell|first=Tom|date=30 June 2015|access-date=19 February 2016|archive-date=2 July 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150702103202/http://www.uefa.com/under21/season=2015/matches/round=2000411/match=2015383/postmatch/report/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Senior===
Cancelo was called up for the first time to [[Portugal national football team|the senior team]] by head coach [[Fernando Santos (footballer, born 1954)|Fernando Santos]] on 26 August 2016,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.portugoal.net/selecao/524-andre-silva-and-joao-cancelo-called-into-portugal-squad|title=André Silva and João Cancelo called into Portugal squad|publisher=PortuGOAL|date=28 August 2016|access-date=29 August 2016|archive-date=29 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160829134349/http://portugoal.net/selecao/524-andre-silva-and-joao-cancelo-called-into-portugal-squad|url-status=live}}</ref> playing the full 90 minutes of a 5–0 friendly win over [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] in [[Porto]] on 1 September and scoring the third goal.<ref>{{cite web |date=1 September 2016 |title=Without Cristiano Ronaldo, Euro champ Portugal routs Gibraltar |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2016/09/01/portugal-gibraltar-friendly-nani-goals |access-date=7 September 2020 |website=SI |language=en-US}}</ref> In the following month he added another two, in as many [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|qualifiers]] against [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] (6–0, home)<ref>{{cite news |title=Cristiano Ronaldo hits four in Portugal's 6-0 rout of nine-man Andorra |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2016/oct/07/portugal-andorra-world-cup-2018-qualifier-cristiano-ronaldo |access-date=7 September 2020 |newspaper=The Guardian |date=7 October 2016 |archive-date=24 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170124232426/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2016/oct/07/portugal-andorra-world-cup-2018-qualifier-cristiano-ronaldo |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]] (away, same score).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=431829|title=Andre Silva nets hat trick as Portugal roll over Faroe Islands|publisher=[[ESPN]]|date=10 October 2016|access-date=21 May 2018|archive-date=3 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703163545/http://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=431829|url-status=live}}</ref>

In May 2018, Cancelo was included in a preliminary 35-man squad for the finals in Russia,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Crawford |first1=Stephen |title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - 23-man & preliminary lists & when will they be announced? |url=https://www.goal.com/brasilglobaltour/en-ca/news/4179/england/2018/05/16/44824112/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists |website=goal.com |access-date=7 September 2020}}</ref> but he did not make the final cut.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/news/portugal-world-cup-squad|title=Nearly half Portugal's Euro squad to miss World Cup|publisher=[[Special Broadcasting Service]]|date=17 May 2018|access-date=17 May 2018|archive-date=5 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505182041/https://www.sbs.com.au/news/nearly-half-portugal-s-euro-squad-to-miss-world-cup|url-status=live}}</ref> Cancelo was selected for all four matches in the league phase of the [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League]] group stage,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/teams/players/250059115--bernardo-silva/statistics/ |title=Bernardo Silva |work=UEFA |access-date=26 February 2019 |archive-date=15 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200415023057/https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/teams/players/250059115--bernardo-silva/statistics/|url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/match/2024021--poland-vs-portugal/ |title=Poland vs Portugal |work=UEFA |access-date=26 February 2019}}</ref> helping the hosts Portugal qualify to [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|the inaugural Nations League Finals]] in June 2019. In the [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|UEFA Nations League Finals]], Portugal defeated the [[Netherlands]] 1–0 in Porto to win the trophy.<ref>{{cite news |first=Daniel |last=Taylor |author-link=Daniel Taylor (journalist) |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jun/09/portugal-netherlands-nations-league-final-match-report |title=Portugal win Nations League as Gonçalo Guedes does for the Netherlands |website=[[The Guardian]] |location=Estádio do Dragão |date=9 June 2019 |access-date=2 February 2020 |archive-date=14 June 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200614133558/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jun/09/portugal-netherlands-nations-league-final-match-report |url-status=live }}</ref>

Cancelo was initially included in Portugal's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2020]] in June 2021; however, he tested positive for [[COVID-19]] two days prior to the team's opening match against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]], and was replaced in the squad by [[Diogo Dalot]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jun/13/joao-cancelo-positive-for-covid-and-replaced-in-portugal-squad-by-diogo-dalot-euro-2020 |title=João Cancelo positive for Covid and replaced in Portugal squad by Dalot |newspaper=The Guardian |date=13 June 2021 |access-date=13 June 2021 |archive-date=13 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210613112805/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jun/13/joao-cancelo-positive-for-covid-and-replaced-in-portugal-squad-by-diogo-dalot-euro-2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In October 2022, he was named in Portugal's preliminary 55-man [[Portugal national football team|squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/rumor-portugal-reportedly-announce-provisional-55-man-squad-2022-fifa-world-cup-liverpool-star-receives-surprise-call|title=Portugal reportedly name provisional 55-man squad for 2022 FIFA World Cup; Liverpool star receives surprise call up|publisher=[[Sportskeeda]]|first=Dakir Mohammed|last=Thanveer|date=25 October 2022|access-date=9 November 2022|archive-date=9 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221109135750/https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/rumor-portugal-reportedly-announce-provisional-55-man-squad-2022-fifa-world-cup-liverpool-star-receives-surprise-call|url-status=live}}</ref> being included in the final 26-man squad for the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/mundial/artigos/os-26-convocados-de-portugal-para-o-mundial2022|title=Os 26 convocados de Portugal: Gonçalo Ramos, António Silva, Otávio e Matheus Nunes chamados|trans-title=Portugal select 26: Gonçalo Ramos, António Silva, Otávio and Matheus Nunes called|publisher=SAPO|language=pt|date=10 November 2022|access-date=10 November 2022|archive-date=10 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221110174203/https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/mundial/artigos/os-26-convocados-de-portugal-para-o-mundial2022|url-status=live}}</ref> Cancelo initially started Portugal's group stage matches, but amid a bad run of form, he lost his place to Diogo Dalot, who started the team's round of 16 game against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]], with Portugal winning the match 6–1.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Brown |first=James Horncastle and Luke |title=Who is Goncalo Ramos — the man who replaced Cristiano Ronaldo |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3976061/2022/12/06/goncalo-ramos-cristiano-ronaldo-portugal/ |date=6 December 2022 |access-date=6 December 2022 |website=The Athletic |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/portugal-switzerland-result-final-score-b2239867.html|title=Who needs Ronaldo? Ramos hat-trick powers Portugal into World Cup quarter-finals|date=7 December 2022|website=The Independent}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/match-centre/match/17/255711/285073/400128130 |title=Portugal 6–1 Switzerland |publisher=FIFA |accessdate=6 December 2022}}</ref> In the quarter-final against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]], Cancelo again started on the bench, coming on for [[Raphaël Guerreiro]] in the 51st minute as Portugal lost 1–0.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 December 2022 |title=Morocco 1-0 Portugal: World Cup 2022 quarter-final – as it happened |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2022/dec/10/morocco-portugal-world-cup-2022-quarter-final-live |access-date=11 December 2022 |website=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Ronaldo equals men's international appearance record |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/ronaldo-equals-mens-international-appearance-record |publisher=FIFA |access-date=17 December 2022 }}</ref>

[[File: Portugal national football team 0866 (João Cancelo).jpg|thumb|upright|Cancelo with [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] in 2025]]
During [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]], Cancelo appeared nine times and scored three goals as Portugal won all ten matches in [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group J|Group J]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/teams/players/250024746--joao-cancelo/matches/|title=João Cancelo - Matches|access-date=3 July 2024|website=UEFA}}</ref> On 21 May 2024, Cancelo was named in Portugal's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]] in Germany.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cx88ljwp5x8o|title=Ronaldo named in Portugal squad for Euro 2024|date=21 May 2024|access-date=3 July 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He started the team's opening match against [[Czechia national football team|Czechia]], where he was substituted for [[Nélson Semedo]] in the 90th minute.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036172--portugal-vs-czechia/lineups/|title=Portugal vs Czechia: Line-ups|access-date=3 July 2024|website=UEFA}}</ref> He then played the first 68 minutes against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036183--turkiye-vs-portugal/lineups/|title=Türkiye vs Portugal: Line-ups|access-date=3 July 2024|website=UEFA}}</ref> assisting [[Samet Akaydin]] 28th-minute own goal. He was rested for the final [[UEFA Euro 2024 Group F|Group F]] fixture against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] which Portugal lost 2–0.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036196--georgia-vs-portugal/|title=Georgia vs Portugal|access-date=3 July 2024|website=UEFA}}</ref> He was restored to the starting line-up for Portugal's [[UEFA Euro 2024 knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]] match against [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]] and played 117 minutes as Portugal won 3–0 in a [[penalty shootout]] after the match ended in a 0–0 draw.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036201--portugal-vs-slovenia/lineups/|title=Portugal vs Slovenia: Line-ups|access-date=3 July 2024|website=UEFA}}</ref> Portugal were eliminated in the quarter-finals to [[France national football team|France]] after losing 5–3 in another penalty shootout.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy79llev4znt|title=Portugal 0–0 France (France win 5–3 on pens)|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Emma|last=Sanders|date=5 July 2024|access-date=6 July 2024}}</ref>

==Style of play==
[[File:João Cancelo USMNT v Portugal Mar 31 2026-102.jpg|thumb|upright|Cancelo with [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] in 2026]]
Cancelo is known for his speed, energy and offensive capabilities, as well as his technique, [[Dribbling (association football)|dribbling skills]], creativity and [[Cross (association football)|crossing]] ability. He is capable of playing as a full back or winger on either flank, although he usually plays on the right.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2017/07/30/597dc068468aebae658b459f.html|title=Cancelo: winger or full-back for Marcelino?|newspaper=Marca|last1=Álvarez|first1=Fernando|last2=Hanlon|first2=Tim|date=30 July 2017|access-date=13 August 2017|archive-date=13 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813105948/http://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2017/07/30/597dc068468aebae658b459f.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Inter/17-08-2017/inter-occhio-cancelo-non-cancello-terzino-piu-d-attacco-che-difesa-2101058967466.shtml|title=Inter, occhio! Cancelo non è un cancello: terzino più d'attacco che di difesa|trans-title=Inter, watch out! Cancelo isn't a gate: more of an attacking full-back than a defensive one|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|last=Brega|first=Matteo|language=it|date=17 August 2017|access-date=24 September 2018|archive-date=10 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180810235551/https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Inter/17-08-2017/inter-occhio-cancelo-non-cancello-terzino-piu-d-attacco-che-difesa-2101058967466.shtml|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="marauding full-back">{{cite web|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/joao-cancelo-marauding-full-back-barcelona-might-replace-dani-alves|title=Joao Cancelo: The marauding full-back Barcelona might replace Dani Alves with|publisher=[[FourFourTwo]]|last=Wilkes|first=Paul|date=29 June 2016|access-date=24 September 2018|archive-date=24 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180924105940/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/joao-cancelo-marauding-full-back-barcelona-might-replace-dani-alves|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kwese.espn.com/football/club/juventus/111/blog/post/3646595/paulo-dybala-an-8-in-juventus-win-and-should-enjoy-confidence-boost|title=Juventus' Paulo Dybala 8/10 and should enjoy confidence boost|publisher=ESPN FC|last=Rzouki|first=Mina|date=26 September 2018|access-date=28 September 2018|archive-date=29 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929041308/http://kwese.espn.com/football/club/juventus/111/blog/post/3646595/paulo-dybala-an-8-in-juventus-win-and-should-enjoy-confidence-boost|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=2 January 2020 |title=Manchester City, Guardiola su Cancelo: "Decida se restare oppure no" |url=https://sport.sky.it/calcio/premier-league/2020/01/02/manchester-city-guardiola-cancelo |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609180744/https://sport.sky.it/calcio/premier-league/2020/01/02/manchester-city-guardiola-cancelo |archive-date=9 June 2020 |access-date=9 June 2020 |publisher=sport.sky.it |language=it}}</ref> During his time at Manchester City, he was considered one of the best full backs in Europe.<ref>{{cite news |last=Edwards |first=John |title=In numbers: Joao Cancelo's excellent year |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/joao-cancelo-2021-premier-league-stats-63776555 |access-date=8 June 2022 |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |archive-date=23 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220523123252/https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/joao-cancelo-2021-premier-league-stats-63776555 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Killen |first1=Stephen |last2=Kandola |first2=Anil |date=30 December 2021 |title=Man City's Cancelo hailed among world's best as he features in teams of season |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/joao-cancelo-man-city-praise-22600725 |access-date=8 June 2022 |website=Manchester Evening News |archive-date=20 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920170618/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/joao-cancelo-man-city-praise-22600725 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=16 April 2022 |title=Top 10 Best Defenders in the World 2022 |url=https://www.notice.com.ng/lifestyle/top-10-best-defenders-in-the-world-2022 |access-date=8 June 2022 |website=Notice |archive-date=20 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920171405/https://www.notice.com.ng/lifestyle/top-10-best-defenders-in-the-world-2022 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=4 April 2022 |title=Top 5 Best Football Fullbacks 2022 |url=https://feedmegoal.com/top-fullbacks/ |access-date=8 June 2022 |website=Feed Me Goal |archive-date=4 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220404111954/https://feedmegoal.com/top-fullbacks/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=14 December 2021 |title=Top 10 best right-backs in the world in 2021 |url=https://khelnow.com/football/top-10-right-backs-in-the-world-in-2021/ |access-date=8 June 2022 |website=Khel Now |archive-date=22 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220922044517/https://khelnow.com/football/top-10-right-backs-in-the-world-in-2021 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Ajith |first=Shambhu |title=5 best Portuguese players in the world right now (2022) |url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/5-best-portuguese-players-world-right-now-2022-ronaldo-jota |access-date=8 June 2022 |website=Sportskeeda |date=17 March 2022 |archive-date=23 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220523123252/https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/5-best-portuguese-players-world-right-now-2022-ronaldo-jota |url-status=live }}</ref> Despite his ability going forward, however, his tactical sense, positioning, and defensive skills have been cited as weaknesses in the media.<ref name="marauding full-back"/><ref>{{cite web |date=5 June 2019 |title=Juve, ecco perché Sarri non vuole Cancelo |url=https://www.calciomercato.com/news/juve-ecco-perche-sarri-non-vuole-cancelo-89472 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609181028/https://www.calciomercato.com/news/juve-ecco-perche-sarri-non-vuole-cancelo-89472 |archive-date=9 June 2020 |access-date=9 June 2020 |publisher=www.calciomercato.com |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2836119-joao-cancelo-says-massimiliano-allegri-instagram-controversy-is-fake-news |title=Joao Cancelo Says Massimiliano Allegri Instagram Controversy Is 'Fake News' |publisher=Bleacher Report |last1=Simpson |first1=Christopher |date=14 May 2019 |access-date=9 June 2020 |archive-date=9 June 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609181022/https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2836119-joao-cancelo-says-massimiliano-allegri-instagram-controversy-is-fake-news |url-status=live }}</ref>

When playing as a traditional full back he times his forward runs well. He tends to move forward when in possession rather than making lung-busting overlapping runs around the outside of a teammate, and he prefers to receive to feet rather than chase through balls. On the ball, he is equally capable of cutting infield from the right as he is going around the outside, and will regularly look to cross with his weaker left foot or drive inside the opposing left back and look to combine with those further forward. He is a very strong dribbler and that ability, combined with the fact he is confident on either foot, makes him extremely difficult to defend against. His speed also allow him to be fast enough that to recover at defensive transitions, and is always aware of the space he leaves behind him when his team attacks.<ref name="StyleofPlay">{{Cite web|url=https://www.coachesvoice.com/cv/joao-cancelo-pep-guardiola-manchester-city/|title=João Cancelo: Premier League Player Watch|access-date=1 November 2021|archive-date=1 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211101151449/https://www.coachesvoice.com/cv/joao-cancelo-pep-guardiola-manchester-city/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In his second season in Manchester City, under manager [[Pep Guardiola]], Cancelo was developed into one of his hybrid players, who plays both at full back and in central midfield in the same game. During City's 4–3–3 formation, when out of possession, Cancelo moved into central midfield alongside [[Rodri (footballer, born 1996)|Rodri]], leaving five players to form their attacking line. With their back three spread wide across the pitch, Cancelo, Rodri and two attacking midfielders often form a box in midfield to overload central areas. If City play centrally, Cancelo is often their target – he has proved brilliant at receiving in central midfield and progressing play with daring and accurate forward passes. Cancelo also become one of City's most effective creative players, often adopting positions in either half-space before delivering a ball into the penalty area or slipping a through ball between defenders. When in a more withdrawn position, Cancelo is adept at moving into central midfield and playing a ball over the top for a runner in behind. With Cancelo instead adding an extra player in midfield, their attack is better set up to deal with defensive transitions.<ref name="StyleofPlay"/>

==Personal life==
In January 2013, Cancelo's mother Filomena was killed in a car accident on the [[A2 motorway (Portugal)|A2 motorway]] in [[Seixal]]. Cancelo and his brother were asleep and received only minor injuries.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sport-english.com/en/news/the-tragic-accident-which-has-shaped-joao-cancelos-career-5171669|title=The tragic accident which has shaped Joao Cancelo's career|newspaper=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]]|date=31 May 2016|access-date=12 February 2018|archive-date=9 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609153354/https://www.sport-english.com/en/news/the-tragic-accident-which-has-shaped-joao-cancelos-career-5171669|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=João Cancelo ferido em acidente que matou a sua mãe |trans-title=João Cancelo injured in accident that killed his mother |url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/joao-cancelo-ferido-em-acidente-que-matou-a-sua-mae-2977590.html |access-date=1 October 2019 |newspaper=Diário de Notícias |date=5 January 2013 |language=pt |archive-date=1 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001195958/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/joao-cancelo-ferido-em-acidente-que-matou-a-sua-mae-2977590.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=João Cancelo construiu a carreira em nome da mãe |trans-title=João Cancelo built a career in the name of his mother |url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/seleccao/interior/joao-cancelo-construiu-a-carreira-em-nome-da-mae-5369845.html |access-date=1 October 2019 |newspaper=Diário de Notícias |date=3 September 2016 |language=pt |archive-date=1 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001200000/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/seleccao/interior/joao-cancelo-construiu-a-carreira-em-nome-da-mae-5369845.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/joao-cancelo-car-crash-mum-16713050.amp|title=The tragedy which has pushed Joao Cancelo to stardom|last=Brennan|first=Stuart|date=7 August 2019|work=Manchester Evening News|access-date=25 September 2021|archive-date=25 September 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210925201237/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/joao-cancelo-car-crash-mum-16713050.amp|url-status=live}}</ref> Due to the emotional toll it took on him, Cancelo considered retiring from football.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Travassos |first=Nuno |date=11 June 2021 |title=João Cancelo: how tragedy became motivation for Portugal's rising star |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jun/11/joao-cancelo-how-tragedy-became-motivation-for-portugals-rising-star |archive-url=https://archive.today/20210611152053/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jun/11/joao-cancelo-how-tragedy-became-motivation-for-portugals-rising-star |archive-date=11 June 2021 |issn=0261-3077 |newspaper=The Guardian}}</ref>

Cancelo and his girlfriend Daniela Machado had a daughter in 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://recordeuropa.com/noticias/cultura-famosos/joao-cancelo-vai-ser-pai-24-06-2019/|title=João Cancelo vai ser pai|trans-title=João Cancelo will be a father|newspaper=Record TV Europa|date=23 June 2019|access-date=12 February 2018|language=pt|archive-date=11 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811225049/https://recordeuropa.com/noticias/cultura-famosos/joao-cancelo-vai-ser-pai-24-06-2019/|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 30 December 2021, their Manchester home was burgled by four men who stole some of his personal jewellery. Cancelo retaliated in self-defence and suffered facial injuries, but said that his family were safe.<ref>{{cite web |title=Joao Cancelo: Manchester City full-back suffers facial injuries after alleged assault and theft |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12506383/joao-cancelo-manchester-city-full-back-suffers-facial-injuries-after-alleged-assault-and-theft |publisher=Sky Sports |access-date=31 December 2021 |date=31 December 2021 |archive-date=4 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221104160620/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12506383/joao-cancelo-manchester-city-full-back-suffers-facial-injuries-after-alleged-assault-and-theft |url-status=live }}</ref>

